6. DFT- DimNIBRSCrimeCategory

Using SSIS Toolbox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard:

Drag and drop the Data Flow - right click Rename it as DFT- DimNIBRSCrimeCategory.

Double click the Data Flow Task –

·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Source – Double click and add the Source connection manager and Data access mode select SQL Command – Copy the below code and paste in the SQL command text box.  And select OK.

select  [NIBRS Crime]
      ,[NIBRS Crime Category]
      ,[NIBRS Crime Against]
      ,[NIBRS Code]
      ,[NIBRS Group]
              from
[DallasCrimeData_Staging].[dbo].[DallasCrimeStaging]
              where [NIBRS Crime] is not null 
              group by [NIBRS Crime]
      ,[NIBRS Crime Category]
      ,[NIBRS Crime Against]
      ,[NIBRS Code]
      ,[NIBRS Group]

·         Drag and drop the derived column - use the Derived column Code and add the as shown in the Gif – Use the code below fig for creating the columns


·         Drag and drop Lookup and configure as follows

1.     General tab – Specify how to handle rows with no matching entries – select Redirect rows to no match output.

2.     Connection tab – OLE DB Connection manger – Select the destination connection manager and Use a table or a view – select DimNIBRSCrimeCategory from the dropdown.

            3.     Columns tab – make connection Source to destination as shown in fig and select OK                                                       

·         Make a Copy of the Lookup and then connect the First lookup to the copied lookup – select the option shown below-


·         Double click the 2nd lookup to go the Column Tab – unselect the NIBRSkey and Match the Column from the source’s column to that in destination’s columns as shown in fig.


·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Command and make connection from the 2nd lookup to it – make connection as shown below fig.



·         Double click the OLE DB command to configure it

1.     Connection Manager Tab – connect to the destination connection manager

2.     Component Properties Tab – in the SQL command – copy and paste the below code   and select OK

Update DimNIBRSCrimeCategory
set
[NIBRSCrime]=?
 ,[NIBRSCrimeAgainst]=?    
,[NIBRSCrimeCategory]=?
      ,[NIBRSCode]=?
      ,[NIBRSGroup]=?
, [RecordFlag] =1
,[EffectiveDate]=getdate()
,[EndDate] = getdate()-1
 
Where [NIBRSKey] =?   

3.     Column Mapping Tab – select the input column as shown in below fig and select OK


·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Destination and make connection from the 1st lookup to it – make connection as shown below fig.


·         Double click on the OLE DB Destination to config it

1.     Connection manager Tab – OLE DB Connection manager – Select the Destination connection manager & Name of the Table or View – Select the DimNIBRSCrimeCategory table

2.     Mapping Tab – Connect the Column as shown in fig and Select OK

[Victim Injury Description], 
  [Victim Condition], 
  [Victim Home Address], 
  [Victim Apartment], 
  [Victim Zip Code], 
  [Victim City], 
  [Victim State] 
from 
 
DallasCrimeData_Staging..DallasCrimeStaging 
where 
  [Victim Name] is not
null 
group by 
  [Victim Name], 
  [Victim Type], 
  [Victim Gender], 
[Victim Injury Description],

  [Victim Home Address],

8. DFT - DimRace

Using SSIS Toolbox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard:

Drag and drop the Data Flow - right click Rename it as DFT - DimRace.

Double click the Data Flow Task –

·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Source – Double click and add the Source connection manager and Data access mode select SQL Command – Copy the below code and paste in the SQL command text box.  And select OK.

select  distinct  [Victim Race]
From DallasCrimeData_Staging..DallasCrimeStaging
where [Victim Race] is not null

·         Drag and drop the derived column - use the Derived column Code and add the as shown in the Gif – Use the code below fig for creating the columns

For Race Column – Copy and paste the Code below in the expression tab

[Victim Race] == "American Indian or Alaska Native" ? " Native American" : ([Victim Race] == "H" ? "Hispanic or Latino" : ([Victim Race] == "NH" ? "Native Hawaiian/Pacific Islander" : ([Victim Race] == "TEST" ? "Unknown" : [Victim Race])))


·         Drag and drop Lookup and configure as follows

1.     General tab – Specify how to handle rows with no matching entries – select Redirect rows to no match output.

2.     Connection tab – OLE DB Connection manger – Select the destination connection manager and Use a table or a view – select DimRace from the dropdown.

3.     Columns tab – make connection Source to destination as shown in fig and select OK                                                       


·         Make a Copy of the Lookup and then connect the First lookup to the copied lookup – select the option shown below-


·         Double click the 2nd lookup to go the Column Tab – unselect the Racekey and Match the Column from the source’s column to that in destination’s columns as shown in fig.


·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Command and make connection from the 2nd lookup to it – make connection as shown below fig.


·         Double click the OLE DB command to configure it

1.     Connection Manager Tab – connect to the destination connection manager

2.     Component Properties Tab – in the SQL command – copy and paste the below code   and select OK

Update [DimRace]
set
[VictimRace] =?
,[RecordFlag] = 1
,[EffectiveDate] = getdate()
,[EndDate] = getdate()-1
 where
[RaceKey] =?

3.     Column Mapping Tab – select the input column as shown in below fig and select OK


·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Destination and make connection from the 1st lookup to it – make connection as shown below fig.


·         Double click on the OLE DB Destination to config it

1.     Connection manager Tab – OLE DB Connection manager – Select the Destination connection manager & Name of the Table or View – Select the DimRace table

2.     Mapping Tab – Connect the Column as shown in fig and Select OK


9. DFT- DimOfficerResponse

Using SSIS Toolbox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard:

Drag and drop the Data Flow - right click Rename it as DFT- DimOfficerResponse.

Double click the Data Flow Task –

·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Source – Double click and add the Source connection manager and Data access mode select SQL Command – Copy the below code and paste in the SQL command text box.  And select OK.

 select 
  [Responding Officer #1  Badge No] , 
  [Responding Officer #1  Name]
from 
DallasCrimeData_Staging..DallasCrimeStaging 
union 
select 
  [Responding Officer #2 Badge No], 
  [Responding Officer #2  Name]
from  
DallasCrimeData_Staging..DallasCrimeStaging 
where 
  [Responding Officer #1  Badge No] is not null and [Responding Officer #1  Name] is not null

·         Drag and drop the derived column - use the Derived column Code and add the as shown in the Gif – Use the code below fig for creating the columns 


·         Drag and drop Lookup and configure as follows

1.     General tab – Specify how to handle rows with no matching entries – select Redirect rows to no match output.

2.     Connection tab – OLE DB Connection manger – Select the destination connection manager and Use a table or a view – select DimOfficerResponse from the dropdown.

3.     Columns tab – make connection Source to destination as shown in fig and select OK                                                       

·         Make a Copy of the Lookup and then connect the First lookup to the copied lookup – select the option shown below-


·         Double click the 2nd lookup to go the Column Tab – unselect the Officerkey and Match the Column from the source’s column to that in destination’s columns as shown in fig.


·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Command and make connection from the 2nd lookup to it – make connection as shown below fig.


·         Double click the OLE DB command to configure it

1.     Connection Manager Tab – connect to the destination connection manager
